race.comment: A good contest. PARTY SPIRIT (11) was in the firing line on the bend narrowly beaten over 1100m at this track when resuming from a spell. Proven second-up and is placed to advantage. Has a soft gate and winning rider Lang is reunited. MISHANI RENEGADE (2) missed the hat-trick in tougher at Eagle Farm and can get back on track at this level. Will go forward again and just needs a touch of luck in that endeavour. An each way hope. OBEROI PRINCESS (8) was beaten a lip here first up and is sure to build on that. Sits handy and can go back-to-back without surprise. BILLIONAIR BABY (6) has been racing well without winning and keeps Ben Thompson. Maps for a soft run must be included.
